imdb.plot outline: Join Norwegian journalist Steinar Ellingsen and his crew as they set out to take on Australia for the first time. The crew consisted of a visual artist, a cameraman and a best boy. Their Australian Odyssey started in Melbourne and finished in the same place ten weeks later, after trekking 16,000 kilometers via Adelaide, Uluru (Ayers Rock), Alice Springs, Darwin, Broome, Perth and everywhere in between. Along the way they visit ecovillages, spot wildlife, interview seemingly random people with great stories to tell, search for UFOs, and they even have a sit-down with royalty.
imdb.title: The Inland Sea: An Australian Odyssey
